30/05/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Culture Minister George Voulgarakis unveiled a plan Tuesday (May 29th) to transfer hundreds of marble statues to a new state-of-the- art Acropolis museum, due to open early next year. 
Voulgarakis said the heavy lifting will begin in September and will cost 2.5m euros. 
Some 340 sculptures, weighing up to 2.5 tonnes each, will be moved a distanceof 400m to the sprawling new museum, in which more than 4,000 exhibits and artifacts will be displayed . 
This is ten times the amount currently on display. 
(Kathimerini - 30/05/07; ANA-MPA, AP, IOL - 29/05/07)
